%N A396202 Decimal expansion of (7 - sqrt(5)) / (7 + sqrt(5)).
%H A396202 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A396202/b396202.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A396202 Kunle Adegoke, <a href="https://www.fq.math.ca/Papers1/55-4/adegoke_infinite_products92117.pdf">Some Infinite Product Identities Involving Fibonacci and Lucas Numbers</a>, The Fibonacci Quarterly, Vol. 55, No. 4 (2017), pp. 343-351.
%H A396202 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_02">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 2</a>.
%F A396202 In the following is phi = (1 + sqrt(5))/2 = A001622.
%F A396202 Equals 22 / (27 + 7*sqrt(5)).
%F A396202 Equals (c - 10)/(c - 5) where c = phi^4*sqrt(5) and phi^4 = A374883.
%F A396202 Equals Limit_{x->oo} abs(a(x) / a(-x)) where a(x) = A396201(x).
%F A396202 A395973 is the solution of phi^(2*x)*cos(Pi*x) = 1/(this constant).
%F A396202 Equals the smallest root of 11 - 27*x + 11*x^2. - _Paolo Xausa_, May 29 2026
%e A396202 0.515796552613703278415262923585503...
%p A396202 Digits := 100: c := (7 - sqrt(5))/(7 + sqrt(5)):
%p A396202 evalf(c, 100)*10^90: ListTools:-Reverse(convert(floor(%), base, 10));
%t A396202 First[RealDigits[22/(27 + 7*Sqrt[5]), 10, 100]] (* _Paolo Xausa_, May 29 2026 *)
%o A396202 (PARI) default(realprecision, 90); polrootsreal(11*x^2 - 27*x + 11)[1]
%Y A396202 Cf. A001622, A396201, A395973, A374883.
%K A396202 nonn,cons,new
%O A396202 0,1
